  "preview": "Looking for like-minded people! Someone thinking in the same direction. Some of my colleagues at Speed and Function are looking for new team members right now. Olga Mykhailova, our Chief Experience Of",
  "text": "Looking for like-minded people! Someone 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘯𝘬𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘪𝘯 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘴𝘢𝘮𝘦 𝘥𝘪𝘳𝘦𝘤𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯. 🎯\n\nSome of my colleagues at Speed and Function are looking for new team members right now.\n\nOlga Mykhailova (Michai), our Chief Experience Officer, is looking for an 𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀 & 𝗖𝘂𝗹𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗠𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗿. She says: \"𝘐'𝘮 𝘩𝘪𝘳𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘢𝘯𝘰𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘳 𝘮𝘦. 𝘓𝘰𝘰𝘬𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘢 𝘱𝘢𝘳𝘵𝘯𝘦𝘳 𝘮𝘢𝘯𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘳 𝘵𝘰 𝘤𝘰𝘯𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘶𝘦 𝘤𝘶𝘭𝘵𝘶𝘳𝘦 𝘳𝘦𝘷𝘰𝘭𝘶𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘢𝘵 𝘚&𝘍 𝘵𝘰𝘨𝘦𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘳 𝘸𝘪𝘵𝘩 𝘮𝘦.\"\n\nNot an executor, but rather a partner in revolution. Could be exciting!🙃\n🧩→ https://lnkd.in/dQF37Xyu\n\nDmytro Batovsky, Head of Solutions Department, is hiring a 𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗖𝗼𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗮𝘁𝗼𝗿 and a 𝗠𝗶𝗱𝗱𝗹𝗲 𝗦𝗼𝗳𝘁𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗘𝗻𝗴𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗲𝗿 (𝗪𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗣𝗿𝗲𝘀𝘀). He puts it this way: \"𝘠𝘰𝘶'𝘳𝘦 𝘥𝘳𝘢𝘸𝘯 𝘵𝘰 𝘱𝘳𝘰𝘫𝘦𝘤𝘵 𝘮𝘢𝘯𝘢𝘨𝘦𝘮𝘦𝘯𝘵 𝘣𝘶𝘵 𝘩𝘢𝘷𝘦𝘯'𝘵 𝘧𝘰𝘶𝘯𝘥 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘳𝘪𝘨𝘩𝘵 𝘱𝘭𝘢𝘤𝘦 𝘵𝘰 𝘥𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘭𝘰𝘱. 𝘔𝘢𝘺𝘣𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘴 𝘪𝘵.\"\nAnd for engineers: \"𝘠𝘰𝘶 𝘸𝘢𝘯𝘵 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘤𝘳𝘢𝘧𝘵 𝘵𝘰 𝘮𝘢𝘵𝘵𝘦𝘳 𝘴𝘰𝘮𝘦𝘸𝘩𝘦𝘳𝘦. 𝘠𝘰𝘶'𝘳𝘦 𝘯𝘰𝘵 𝘫𝘶𝘴𝘵 𝘭𝘰𝘰𝘬𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘧𝘰𝘳 𝘵𝘢𝘴𝘬𝘴.\"\n🧩→ https://lnkd.in/dgCYdCXQ\n\nAnd we're also looking for an 𝗘𝘅𝗲𝗰𝘂𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗻𝗲𝗿 — someone to run the CEO's operating system: work, relationships, and life logistics. This is not a traditional EA role. It's CEO ops plus project execution plus relationship operations.\n🧩 → https://lnkd.in/dHRkDwqN\n\nWe're not filling positions, we're looking for people who 𝘨𝘦𝘵 𝘪𝘵.\n\nAt S&F, culture isn't just a nice-to-have — it's how we actually operate. We believe organizations prosper when they align with people's strongest motive: 𝘵𝘰 𝘨𝘳𝘰𝘸. Not through occasional off-sites or once-a-year coaching. But through daily routines, regular conversations, the way we work together. Development woven into the fabric, not bolted on top. 🌱\n\nIf someone comes to mind, please, share this.",
